e wanting to move from one&#39;s small dilapidated h=\r\nouse (this\n body-mind complex) to a huge palace (realized Self) may first c=\r\nonstruct the palace over time and move into it when it is COMPLETE. Alterna=\r\ntely, if one occasionally goes and stays in the palace still under construc=\r\ntion (analogy for out of body experiences due to Kundalini rise), is it an =\r\nachievement? In fact, it comes with risks. The former approach is safer and=\r\n one loses nothing in it. Similarly, one can progress towards complete Self=\r\n-realization without any out of body experiences. These are not my word&#39;s, =\r\nbut Maharshi Vasishtha&#39;s words to Lord Rama.\n&gt;&gt;=A0\n&gt;&gt;Secondly, one does not=\r\n get something without wanting it and putting sufficient effort towards it.=\r\n One may have deeply desired a Kundalini rise in a previous life and may ha=\r\nve put enough effort. As a result, one may be getting it now. But one may b=\r\ne unprepared (and ironically may not even want it!) when it comes in this l=\r\nife.\n&gt;&gt;=A0\n&gt;&gt;As you do sadhana, try not to fancy too many specific\n desires=\r\n. Nature has a delay mechanism in granting your desires (because of constra=\r\nints on what Nature can give you right now, arising from YOUR\n OWN previous=\r\n actions). So Nature sometimes gives you what you want LATE, when you no lo=\r\nnger want it or want something else. For example, one may pray for great we=\r\nalth one&#39;s whole life and be born as a rich but very sick man in next life.=\r\n One may not enjoy that wealth and pray whole life for health. In the life =\r\nafter that, one may be very healthy, but not have any knowledge or money. I=\r\nn another \ncase, one may deeply desire to act in a famous film. One may be =\r\nreborn \nas a tiger or a dog and act in a famous film, but not really enjoy =\r\nthat \nexperience. Basically, people keep going in circles through various l=\r\nives, always &quot;seeking&quot; something they are &quot;missing&quot;.\n&gt;&gt;=A0\n&gt;&gt;Anyway, coming=\r\n back to Kundalini, if one deeply desires an out of body experience given b=\r\ny a rising Kundalini and one&#39;s previous karmas constrain one from having it=\r\n in THIS life, one may be born in next life with this specific desire desti=\r\nned to fructify (if there is enough karmik force behind it).\n&gt;&gt;=A0\n&gt;&gt;*=A0=\r\n=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0\n *\n&gt;&gt;=A0\n&gt;&gt;Kundalini rise is not =\r\nnecessarily scary or painful, if one is well-prepared in terms of attitude =\r\nand detachment.\n&gt;&gt;=A0\n&gt;&gt;Once I saw a chipmunk glued to a mouse trap. I went=\r\n to free it and it panicked so badly and started to shake violently. I went=\r\n to save it from a certain slow death and it was scared that I would kill i=\r\nt!\n&gt;&gt;=A0\n&gt;&gt;We are like that chipmunk, glued to the mouse trap called this b=\r\nody-mind complex and scared of being rescued from a certain slow death!\n&gt;&gt;=\r\n=A0\n&gt;&gt;If our ideas about who we are (viz this current body-mind complex) ar=\r\ne incorrect and if we are this &quot;infinite Self&quot; as shastras say, won&#39;t a com=\r\nplete realization of that at some stage involve stepping out of this body-m=\r\nind complex, without being scared?\n&gt;&gt;=A0\n&gt;&gt;*=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *=A0=A0=\r\n=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *\n&gt;&gt;=A0\n&gt;&gt;Kundalini rise after most undesirable conditionin=\r\ng is overcome, is far better than\n Kundalini rise forced when some really u=\r\nndesirable conditioning is still left in one&#39;s system.\n&gt;&gt;=A0\n&gt;&gt;When one tra=\r\nnscends one problematic notion about who one is and what one needs, another=\r\n notion that lay buried deeper in consciousness may spring to the surface a=\r\nnd torment one. If one overcomes the notion &quot;I am the body&quot;, there may be a=\r\nnother notion in one&#39;s body-mind complex that one&#39;s awareness clings on to =\r\n(e.g. a great doctor, a great leader, a great scholar, a great saint etc). =\r\nAs an extreme example, if one person had a hidden deep desire to be a great=\r\n soul who rescues the world, he may fancy that he is a re-incarnated X or Y=\r\n who will rescue the world now. When one&#39;s self-awareness (i.e. Kundalini!)=\r\n deeply clings to any such notion, it can cause havoc. The person may show =\r\nsome signs of progress and yet remain in ignorance and get stuck badly.\n&gt;&gt;=\r\n=A0\n&gt;&gt;An awakened Kundalini in a system with undesirable conditioning may a=\r\nccentuate one&#39;s weaknesses and wrong notions heavily and cause serious psyc=\r\nhiatric and spiritual problems.\n&gt;&gt;=A0\n&gt;&gt;*=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *=A0=A0=A0=\r\n=A0=A0=A0=A0 *\n&gt;&gt;=A0\n&gt;&gt;The best approach I recommend is to NOT think in ter=\r\nms of Kundalini and its rise. Just do sadhana, overcome your\n weaknesses an=\r\nd improve your detachment over time. Again, I want to emphasize that detach=\r\nment is not disgust or distaste for life/things/people around you. Disgust =\r\nis the other side of coin of attachment. It is a negative attachment.\n&gt;&gt;=A0=\r\n\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;Don&#39;t worry about \nwhether your Kundalini rises or not. Worry about w=\r\nhether you are able to resist 6 internal enemies (shadripus) and 8 bondages=\r\n (ashta pashas) or \nnot. If your ability to resist them is increasing, you =\r\nare making progress. EVEN IF your Kundalini is fast asleep, you are still m=\r\naking progress. When you completely overcome them, Kundalini (your self-awa=\r\nreness) \nwill automatically ascend to the top and meet Her Lord (true Self)=\r\n.\n&gt;&gt;=A0\n&gt;&gt;*=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *\n&gt;&gt;=A0\n&gt;&gt;One word =\r\non surrendering to a personal deity. Though true surrender is helpful, most=\r\n people do not have it. They simply do business with god. Though people may=\r\n be offended by my words, this is the plain and bare fact.\n&gt;&gt;=A0\n&gt;&gt;&quot;I want =\r\nX, I will pray to you and please give it to me&quot;, &quot;I am scared of Kundalini =\r\nrise, I will pray to you and please protect me&quot; - all this is just a busine=\r\nss deal. There is something you want and you ask god for it. True surrender=\r\n has no place for agendas, desires, demands or expectations. True surrender=\r\n is losing oneself in one&#39;s fascination for the qualities of Lord. True sur=\r\nrender is accepting anything Lord throws one&#39;s way (whether it is pleasurab=\r\nle or highly painful) as Lord&#39;s prasad and accepting it gratefully. True su=\r\nrrender is thinking of Lord with fascination and pleasure, even in the face=\r\n of (and during) Death.\n&gt;&gt;=A0\n&gt;&gt;If one without true surrender and with many=\r\n desires and wrong notions experiences a Kundalini rise, one may still be t=\r\nrapped, despite thinking of a personal god. It is not that god does not wan=\r\nt to &quot;protect&quot; one as said below. It is not about protecting or endangering=\r\n. If you go back to my &quot;chipmunk glued to mouse trap&quot; example above, I was =\r\ntrying to protect it, but it was scared. Similarly, one&#39;s conditioning make=\r\ns one *run away* from God&#39;s\n protection! God&#39;s protection may seem to a con=\r\nditioned mind like grave danger that one should run away from!\n&gt;&gt;=A0\n&gt;&gt;*=A0=\r\n=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *\n&gt;&gt;=A0\n&gt;&gt;Whether through the pat=\r\nh of wisdom or surrender, develop dispassion and detachment. Realize that a=\r\nll this is temporary and can be taken away anytime. Enjoy it while you have=\r\n and keep doing your best, but be prepared to lose everything anytime. Only=\r\n detachment and a very light mental conditioning (very light desires, disli=\r\nkes etc) can protect one as one&#39;s Kundalini rises to meet True Self. Heavy =\r\nconditioning and impurities in one&#39;s nadis will distract rising Kundalini (=\r\nself-awareness) and stop Her from meeting