ing in it. Simila=\r\nrly, one can progress towards complete Self-realization without any out of =\r\nbody experiences. These are not my word&#39;s, but Maharshi Vasishtha&#39;s words t=\r\no Lord Rama.&lt;br&gt;\n&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Secondly, one does not get something without wan=\r\nting it and putting sufficient effort towards it. One may have deeply desir=\r\ned a Kundalini rise in a previous life and may have put enough effort. As a=\r\n result, one may be getting it now. But one may be unprepared (and ironical=\r\nly may not even want it!) when it comes in this life.&lt;br&gt;\n&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;As you =\r\ndo sadhana, try not to fancy too many specific\n desires. Nature has a delay=\r\n mechanism in granting your desires (because of constraints on what Nature =\r\ncan give you right now, arising from YOUR\n OWN previous actions). So Nature=\r\n sometimes gives you what you want LATE, when you no longer want it or want=\r\n something else. For example, one may pray for great wealth one&#39;s whole lif=\r\ne and be born as a rich but very sick man in next life. One may not enjoy t=\r\nhat wealth and pray whole life for health. In the life after that, one may =\r\nbe very healthy, but not have any knowledge or money. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;In anoth=\r\ner \ncase, one may deeply desire to act in a famous film. One may be reborn =\r\n\nas a tiger or a dog and act in a famous film, but not really enjoy that \ne=\r\nxperience. Basically, people &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;keep going in circles through var=\r\nious lives, always &quot;seeking&quot; something they are &quot;missing&quot;.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Any=\r\nway, coming back to Kundalini, if one deeply desires an out of body experie=\r\nnce given by a rising Kundalini and one&#39;s previous karmas constrain one fro=\r\nm having it in THIS life, one may be born in next life with this specific d=\r\nesire destined to fructify (if there is enough karmik force behind it).&lt;br&gt;=\r\n\n&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&=\r\nnbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n *&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Kundalini rise is not necessarily s=\r\ncary or painful, if one is well-prepared in terms of attitude and detachmen=\r\nt.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Once I saw a chipmunk glued to a mouse trap. I went to free=\r\n it and it panicked so badly and started to shake violently. I went to save=\r\n it from a certain slow death and it was scared that I would kill it!&lt;br&gt;\n&=\r\nnbsp;&lt;br&gt;We are like that chipmunk, glued to the mouse trap called this bod=\r\ny-mind complex and scared of being rescued from a certain slow death!&lt;br&gt;&n=\r\nbsp;&lt;br&gt;If our ideas about who we are (viz this current body-mind complex) =\r\nare incorrect and if we are this &quot;infinite Self&quot; as shastras say, won&#39;t a c=\r\nomplete realization of that at some stage involve stepping out of this body=\r\n-mind complex, without being scared?&lt;br&gt;\n&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp=\r\n;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;=\r\n&lt;br&gt;Kundalini rise after most undesirable conditioning is overcome, is far =\r\nbetter than\n Kundalini rise forced when some really undesirable conditionin=\r\ng is still left in one&#39;s system.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;When one transcends one probl=\r\nematic notion about who one is and what one needs, another notion that lay =\r\nburied deeper in consciousness may spring to the surface and torment one. I=\r\nf one overcomes the notion &quot;I am the body&quot;, there may be another notion in =\r\none&#39;s body-mind complex that one&#39;s awareness clings on to (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;sp=\r\nan&gt;e.g. a great doctor, a great leader, a great scholar, a great saint etc&lt;=\r\n/span&gt;). As an extreme example, if one person had a hidden deep desire to b=\r\ne a great soul who rescues the world, he may fancy that he is a re-incarnat=\r\ned X or Y who will rescue the world now. When one&#39;s self-awareness (i.e. Ku=\r\nndalini!) deeply clings to any such notion, it can cause havoc. The person =\r\nmay show some signs of progress and yet remain in ignorance and get stuck\n =\r\nbadly.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;An awakened Kundalini in a system with undesirable cond=\r\nitioning may accentuate one&#39;s weaknesses and wrong notions heavily and caus=\r\ne serious psychiatric and spiritual problems.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nb=\r\nsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;b=\r\nr&gt;\n&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;The best approach I recommend is to NOT think in terms of Kund=\r\nalini and its rise. Just do sadhana, overcome your\n weaknesses and improve =\r\nyour detachment over time. Again, I want to emphasize that detachment is no=\r\nt disgust or distaste for life/things/people around you. Disgust is the oth=\r\ner side of coin of attachment.&lt;/span&gt; It is a negative attachment.&lt;br&gt;\n&nbs=\r\np;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;font-style:normal;font-size:13.3333px;background-=\r\ncolor:transparent;font-family:arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;D&lt;span&gt;on&#39;t wo=\r\nrry about \nwhether your Kundalini rises or not. Worry about whether you are=\r\n able to\n resist 6 internal enemies (shadripus) and 8 bondages (ashta pasha=\r\ns) or \nnot. If your ability to resist them is increasing, you are making pr=\r\nogress. EVEN IF your Kundalini is fast asleep, you are still making progres=\r\ns. When you completely overcome them, Kundalini (your self-awareness) \nwill=\r\n automatically ascend to the top and meet Her Lord (true Self).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div=\r\n&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;font-style:normal;font-size:13px;background-color:transparen=\r\nt;font-family:arial, helvetica, clean, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span&gt;*&nbsp;=\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&=\r\nnbsp; *&lt;br&gt;\n&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;One word on surrendering to a personal deity. Though =\r\ntrue surrender is helpful, most people do not have it. They simply do busin=\r\ness with god. Though people may be offended by my words, this is the plain =\r\nand bare fact.&lt;br&gt;\n&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&quot;I want X, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;I will pray to y=\r\nou and &lt;/span&gt;please give it to me&quot;, &quot;I am scared of Kundalini rise, I will=\r\n pray to you and please protect\n me&quot; - all this is just a business deal. Th=\r\nere is something you want and you ask god for it. True surrender has no pla=\r\nce for agendas, desires, demands or expectations. True surrender is losing =\r\noneself in one&#39;s fascination for the qualities of Lord. True surrender is a=\r\nccepting anything Lord throws one&#39;s way (whether it is pleasurable or highl=\r\ny painful) as Lord&#39;s prasad and accepting it gratefully. True surrender is =\r\nthinking of Lord with fascination and pleasure, even in the face of (and du=\r\nring) Death.&lt;br&gt;\n&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;If one without true surrender and with many desi=\r\nres and wrong notions experiences a Kundalini rise, one may still be trappe=\r\nd, despite thinking of a personal god. It is not that god does not want to =\r\n&quot;protect&quot; one as said below. It is not about protecting or endangering. If =\r\nyou go back to my &quot;chipmunk glued to mouse trap&quot; example above, I was tryin=\r\ng to protect it, but it was scared. Similarly, one&#39;s conditioning makes one=\r\n *run away* from God&#39;s\n protection! God&#39;s protection may seem to a conditio=\r\nned mind like grave danger that one should run away from!&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/sp=\r\nan&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nb=\r\nsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Whether through the path =\r\nof wisdom or surrender, develop dispassion and detachment. Realize that all=\r\n this is temporary and can be taken away anytime. Enjoy it while you have a=\r\nnd keep doing your best, but be prepared to lose everything anytime. Only d=\r\netachment and a very light mental conditioning (very light desires, dislike=\r\ns etc) can protect one as one&#39;s Kundalini rises to meet True Self. Heavy co=\r\nnditioning and impurities in one&#39;s nadis will distract rising Kundalini (se=\r\nlf-awareness) and stop Her from meeting True Self.&lt;br&gt;\n&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;The real k=\r\ney is how light your conditioning is.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Best\n regards,&lt;br=\r\n&gt;Narasimha&lt;br&gt;--------&lt;br&gt;Astrology &amp; Spirituality Resources: &lt;a rel=3D=\r\n&quot;nofollow&quot; target=3D&quot;_blank&quot; href=3D&quot;http://www.vedicastrologer.org/&quot;&gt;http:=\r\n//www.VedicAstrologer.org&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;font-style:normal;font-siz=\r\ne:13px;background-color:transparent;font-family:arial, helvetica, clean, sa=\r\nns-serif;&quot;&gt;\n--------&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;blockquote style=3D&quot;border-le=\r\nft:2px solid rgb(16,16,255);margin-left:5px;margin-top:5px;padding-left:5px=\r\n;&quot;&gt;  &lt;div style=3D&quot;font-family:arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:10pt;=\r\n&quot;&gt; &lt;div style=3D&quot;font-family:times new roman, new york, times, serif;font-s=\r\nize:12pt;&quot;&gt;\n &lt;div dir=3D&quot;ltr&quot;&gt; &lt;font face=3D&quot;Arial&quot;&gt; &lt;hr size=3D&quot;1&quot;&gt;  &lt;b&gt;&lt;s=\r\npan style=3D&quot;font-weight:bold;&quot;&gt;From:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt; Leela Sastry &lt;&lt;a href=\r\n=3D&quot;&quot; rel=3D&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;leela.sastry@...&lt;/a&gt;&gt;&lt;br&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=3D=\r\n&quot;font-weight:bold;&quot;&gt;To:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt; &quot;&lt;a href=3D&quot;&quot; rel=3D&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;vedic-wis=\r\ndom@yahoogroups.com&lt;/a&gt;&quot; &lt;&lt;a href=3D&quot;&quot; rel=3D&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;vedic-wisdom@yah=\r\noogroups.com&lt;/a&gt;&gt