ation. We have not be=\r\nen able to find anything physically wrong with her (all tests normal)- so i=\r\nt might be that this is due to deranged kundalini. Many people we call ment=\r\nally ill describe themselves as having a spiritual crisis, or unwanted spon=\r\ntaneous kundalini awakening- this has triggered interest and research into =\r\nthis topic in mainstream psychiatry. Unfortunately these patients are not w=\r\nell-understood by western medicine, and as we have no treatments\n for deran=\r\nged kundalini, we struggle to help them. Many yogis try to forcibly waken t=\r\nhe kundalini. My experience with this lady confirmed my feeling that kundal=\r\nini should not be forcibly wakened. This woman wants to kill herself at tim=\r\nes because the suffering from the deranged energy is so bad. She feels it w=\r\nill consume her, and it is something she cannot escape from. I wondered wha=\r\nt solution there could be to her problem. The logical one was to pray to th=\r\ne Divine Mother, who manifests as the kundalini to relieve the suffering of=\r\n this woman- and either cure her, or give her the strength to bear this. Ma=\r\ny I request that the good samaritans among you pray for her, and for others=\r\n like her (whom we may not know of)- their suffering really is pitiable. An=\r\nd let us be careful in our sadhana so as not to end up in this situation ou=\r\nrselves. Perhaps this is why the bhakti marga is the safest. It is perhaps =\r\nsafest to say &quot;let me be your\n instrument&quot; and leave the kundalini rising b=\r\nit to God&#39;s will. Om Dum Durgayai Namaha Aparna &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/d=\r\niv&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt; \n\n  =\r\n  &lt;/div&gt;\n     \n\n    \n    &lt;div style=3D&quot;color:#fff;min-height:0;&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n\n  =\r\n      \n  \n  \n    &lt;table style=3D&quot;margin-top:20px;margin-botto